knight fellowships class of 2009 isra al rubei i knight fellowships isra al rubei i isra al rubei i international fellow isra stanford edu reporter national public radio baghdad study focus freedom of the press in post conflict societies and the development of media in emerging democracies born and raised in baghdad iraq al rubei i earned her bachelor's degree from baghdad university and her master's from al mustansiriya university based in baghdad throughout her life and career rubei i had her first journalism assignment in 1993 as a reporter for the baghdad observer the only english language newspaper in iraq at the time in 2003 when saddam hussein's regime was overthrown she started with ard german radio as a reporter since early 2004 she has been a reporter for national public radio covering the iraq war and politics fellows are listed with original titles and employers from their fellowship year stanford university
